      "rationale": "Full model input inventory documented for 23 inputs: pump geometry (nominal dimensions from CMM measurements ±0.01 mm, tolerances per engineering drawing), blood density (1055 ± 5 kg/m³), Carreau viscosity model constants (fit to rheometry data R²=0.997), hemolysis power-law constants (C=3.62e-7, alpha=2.416, beta=0.785 from Giersiepen 1990 with literature uncertainty bounds), inlet velocity profile (from PIV measurements), outlet pressure (from bench test calibrated transducer ±0.5 mmHg). UQ propagation via Latin hypercube sampling confirms NIH sensitivity dominated by power-law constants (±10%) and geometric tolerances (±4%). Exceeds Gradation 2 requirement."
